<subSubSection id="C34472A7FFE6683B459A366DBF5EFC29" pageId="19" pageNumber="302" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE1212CFFE6683B459A366DBF5EFC29" blockId="19.[151,1437,762,933]" pageId="19" pageNumber="302">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFE6683B459A366DBB4FFC0D" bold="true" box="[199,308,870,896]" pageId="19" pageNumber="302">Remarks</emphasis>
. These are the first male and females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E5AAFFFE6683B4655366CB9E8FC0D" authorityName="Neboiss" authorityYear="1980" box="[776,915,870,896]" class="Insecta" family="Dipseudopsidae" genus="Hyalopsyche" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="disjuncta">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFE6683B4655366CB9E8FC0D" box="[776,915,870,896]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="302">H. disjuncta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
recorded outside of northeastern 
<collectingRegion id="499AEFCEFFE6683B404C366DBFE2FC0D" box="[1297,1433,870,896]" country="Australia" name="Queensland" pageId="19" pageNumber="302">Queensland</collectingRegion>
. Larvae were previously recorded from northern NSW and the Roper River in the NT (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF5CDDFFE6683B41073681BF63FC29" author="Cartwright, D. I." box="[1114,1304,906,932]" pageId="19" pageNumber="302" pagination="1 - 28" refId="ref14591" refString="Cartwright, D. I. (1998) Preliminary guide to the identification of late instar larvae of Australian Polycentropodidae, Glossosomatidae, Dipsuedopsidae and Psychomyiidae (Insecta: Trichoptera). Co-operative Research Centre for Freshwater Ecology Identification Guide, 15, 1 - 28." type="journal article" year="1998">Cartwright 1998</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
